<subSubSection pageId="74" pageNumber="75" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="74.[151,1437,151,935]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,802,827]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin participle of the verb “ 
<emphasis box="[773,845,804,827]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">omitto</emphasis>
”, meaning to leave out or omit, referring to the lack of a sex patch on tergite 
<number box="[426,442,838,863]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" value="5.0">5</number>
, although a well developed sex patch is present on tergite 
<number box="[1095,1111,839,863]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" value="4.0">4</number>
, a unique character state that defines the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
